@node "36_BAD_DISK" "36_BAD_DISK"
 basic_error/36_BAD_DISK                                 basic_error/36_BAD_DISK
 
 NUMBER
     36

 MESSAGE
     BAD DISK

 DESCRIPTION
     An attempt failed to HEADER a disk, because the quick header method 
     (no ID) was attempted on an unformatted disk, or the disk is bad.
@endnode

@node "Disk Error Messages" "Disk Error Messages"

 DISK ERROR MESSAGES
 
     These error messages are returned through the @{"DS" link "DS" 0} and @{"DS$" link "DS$" 0} reserved 
     variables.
 
         NUM.    MESSAGE                     NUM.    MESSAGE
 
         01      <deleted>                   @{"71      DIRECTORY ERROR         " link "71_DIRECTORY_ERROR" 0}
         02      -                           @{"72      DISK FULL               " link "72_DISK_FULL" 0}
         03      -                           @{"29      DISK ID MISMATCH        " link "29_DISK_ID_MISMATCH" 0}
         04      -                           @{"73      DOS MISMATCH            " link "73_DOS_MISMATCH" 0}
         05      -                           @{"74      DRIVE NOT READY         " link "74_DRIVE_NOT_READY" 0}
         06      -                           @{"63      FILE EXISTS             " link "63_FILE_EXISTS" 0}
